{"title_page": "Before the Flood (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2016 film by Fisher Stevens}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Before the Flood'' (film)}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Before the Flood\n| image          = Before the Flood (2016 documentary film) poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Fisher Stevens]]\n| producer       = {{plainlist|\n* Fisher Stevens\n* [[Leonardo DiCaprio]]\n* Jennifer Davisson\n* [[James Packer]]\n* [[Brett Ratner]]\n* Trevor Davidoski\n}}\n| writer         = Mark Monroe\n| starring       = \n| narrator       = Leonardo DiCaprio  \n| music          = {{plainlist|\n* [[Gustavo Santaolalla]]\n* [[Trent Reznor]]\n* [[Atticus Ross]]\n* [[Mogwai]]\n}}\n| cinematography = Antonio Rossi\n| editing        = Brett Banks<br>Geoffrey Rickman<br>Abhay Sofsky<br>Ben Sozanski\n| studio         = [[Appian Way Productions|Appian Way]]<br>[[RatPac-Dune Entertainment|RatPac Documentary Films]]<br>Insurgent Docs<br>Mandarin Film Productions\n| distributor    = [[National Geographic Society|National Geographic Documentary Films]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2016|10|21}}\n| runtime        = 96 minutes<ref name=hollywood>{{cite news |last=DeFore |first=John |date=9 September 2016 |title='Before the Flood': Film Review - TIFF 2016 |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/before-flood-927190 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=10 September 2016 }}</ref>\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n| image_size     = \n}}\n'''''Before the Flood''''' is a 2016 [[documentary film]] about [[global warming|climate change]] directed by [[Fisher Stevens]]. The film was produced as a collaboration between Stevens, [[Leonardo DiCaprio]], [[James Packer]], [[Brett Ratner]], Trevor Davidoski, and Jennifer Davisson Killoran. [[Martin Scorsese]] is an executive producer.<ref name=Imdb>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5929776|title=Before the Flood|accessdate=9 September 2016|publisher=IMDB}}</ref>\n\nThe film premiered at the [[Toronto International Film Festival]] in September 2016, and was released theatrically on October 21, before airing on the [[National Geographic Channel]] on October 30.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/dicaprio-unveils-climate-change-film-before-the-flood/2016/09/09/2d279598-76fb-11e6-9781-49e591781754_story.html |title=DiCaprio unveils climate change film \u2018Before the Flood\u2019 |agency=Associated Press |location=''[[The Washington Post]]'' |date=9 September 2016 |access-date=10 September 2016 }}</ref><ref name=\"national-geographic-2016\">{{cite web|url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/2016/10/obama-leonardo-dicaprio-white-house-lawn-before-the-flood-btf/ |title=President Obama Urges Swift Action on Climate Change |publisher=News.nationalgeographic.com |date= |accessdate=2016-10-24}}</ref> As part of National Geographic's commitment to covering climate change, the documentary was made widely available and free of charge on various platforms.<ref name=\"ecowatch-2016\">{{cite web \n | first = Lorraine | last = Chow\n | title = Watch Leonardo DiCaprio's climate change doc online for free\n | work = EcoWatch\n | date = 25 October 2016\n | url = http://www.ecowatch.com/leonardo-dicaprio-before-the-flood-2062971522.html\n | access-date = 2016-10-27\n}}</ref> \n==Background==\nAt the European [[premiere]] in London in October 2016, DiCaprio introduced the film as follows:\n\n{{quote|''Before The Flood'' is the product of an incredible three-year journey that took place with my co-creator and director Fisher Stevens. We went to every corner of the globe to document the devastating impacts of climate change and questioned humanity's ability to reverse what may be the most catastrophic problem mankind has ever faced. There was a lot to take in. All that we witnessed on this journey shows us that our world's climate is incredibly interconnected and that it is at urgent breaking point.{{nbsp}}... We wanted to create a film that gave people a sense of urgency, that made them understand what particular things are going to solve this problem. We bring up the issue of a carbon tax, for example, which I haven't seen in a lot of documentaries. Basically, sway a capitalist economy to try to invest in renewables, to bring less money and subsidies out of oil companies. These are the things that are really going to make a massive difference.{{nbsp}}... We need to use our vote{{nbsp}}... We cannot afford to have political leaders out there that do not believe in modern science or the scientific method or empirical truths{{nbsp}}... We cannot afford to waste time having people in power that choose to believe in the 2{{nbsp}}percent of the scientific community that is basically bought off by lobbyists and oil companies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecowatch.com/leonardo-dicaprio-before-the-flood-2057070140.html|title=7 Key Scenes in Leonardo DiCaprio's Climate Film 'Before the Flood'}}</ref>}}\n\n==Content==\n[[File:The Garden of Earthly Delights by Bosch High Resolution.jpg|thumb|[[The Garden of Earthly Delights]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-painting/|title=Before the Flood - Painting|website=Before the Flood}}</ref>]]\n\nThe film shows DiCaprio visiting various regions of the globe<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-capsule-before-the-flood-review-20161017-snap-story.html|title=Leonardo DiCaprio crosses the globe in the climate change documentary 'Before the Flood'|last=Times|first=Los Angeles|website=latimes.com|access-date=2016-11-01}}</ref> exploring the impact of [[global warming]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wired.it/attualita/ambiente/2016/10/30/before-the-flood-dicaprio/|title=Guarda Before the Flood, il documentario di DiCaprio contro il cambiamento climatico - Wired|date=2016-10-30|newspaper=Wired|language=it-IT|access-date=2016-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031142830/http://www.wired.it/attualita/ambiente/2016/10/30/before-the-flood-dicaprio/|archive-date=2016-10-31|url-status=dead}}</ref> As a narrator, DiCaprio comments these encounters as well as archive footages. DiCaprio repeatedly references a 15th-century [[triptych]] by [[Hieronymus Bosch]], ''[[The Garden of Earthly Delights]]'', which, he explains, hung above his crib as an infant, and which he uses as an analogy of the present course of the world toward<!-- UK English favours \"towards\" but this is a US film --> potential ruin as depicted on its final panel.<ref>{{cite web|title=DiCaprio\u2019s \u2018Before the Flood\u2019 explores a different inconvenient truth: Human nature|publisher=Fusion|url=http://fusion.net/story/364193/dicaprios-before-the-flood-explores-a-different-inconvenient-truth-human-nature/|accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref> The film also documents, in part, the production of DiCaprio's 2015 film ''[[The Revenant (2015 film)|The Revenant]]''.\n\nDiCaprio's comments and inquiries focus extensively on [[climate change denial]], mostly among corporate lobbyists and politicians of the United States.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/article/leonardo-dicaprio-before-the-flood|title=Leonardo DiCaprio almost died making his documentary Before The Flood|last=Halls|first=Eleanor|newspaper=British GQ|language=en-GB|access-date=2016-11-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ctvnews.ca/entertainment/director-horrified-by-alta-oilsands-scenes-in-dicaprio-s-before-the-flood-1.3132335|title=Director 'horrified' by Alta. oilsands scenes in DiCaprio's 'Before The Flood'|newspaper=CTVNews|access-date=2016-11-10}}</ref>\n\nThey interview with British-born astronaut [[Piers Sellers]], a [[NASA]] scientist who flew on three space missions, discusses his desire to publicize the perils of global warming in the short time he expected he had remaining to live, as he had stage IV pancreatic cancer as he was being filmed. He died on December 23, 2016.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/science/2016/dec/24/climate-scientist-and-nasa-astronaut-piers-sellers-dies-aged-61 Climate scientist and Nasa astronaut Piers Sellers dies aged 61], ''[[The Guardian]]'', December 24, 2016. Retrieved April 23, 2019.</ref>\n\n==Cast==\nAlong with DiCaprio, the documentary's subjects include [[Piers Sellers]], [[Barack Obama]], [[Pope Francis]], [[Sunita Narain]], [[Anote Tong]], [[John Kerry]], [[Elon Musk]], [[Alejandro Gonz\u00e1lez I\u00f1\u00e1rritu]], [[Johan Rockstr\u00f6m]], [[Greg Mankiw]], [[Gidon Eshel]], [[Farwiza Farhan]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/farwiza-farhan/|title=Before the Flood - Farwiza Farhan|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> Ian Singleton,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/doctor-ian-singleton-phd/|title=Before the Flood - Dr. Ian Singleton, Ph.D|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> Lindsey Allen,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/lindsey-allen/|title=Before the Flood - Lindsey Allen|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> Jeremy Jackson,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/jeremy-jackson/|title=Before the Flood - Jeremy Jackson|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> Thomas Esang Remengesau Jr.,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/thomas-esang-tommy-remengesau-jr/|title=Before the Flood - Thomas Esang \"Tommy\" Remengesau, Jr.|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> Alvin Lin,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/alvin-lin/|title=Before the Flood - Alvin Lin|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> [[Ma Jun (environmentalist)|Ma Jun]], [[Michael E. Mann]], [[Philip Levine (politician)|Philip Levine]], [[Jason Box|Jason E. Box]],  Dr. [[Enric Sala]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/doctor-enric-sala/|title=Before the Flood - Dr. Enric Sala|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> [[Michael Brune]], and [[Ban Ki-moon|Ban Ki-Moon]].<ref name=hollywood /><ref name=\"national-geographic-2016\"/>\n\nSubjects for the DVD's extra or deleted scenes include: [[Mark Z. Jacobson|Steven Z. Jacobson]], [[Steven Chu]], Andrew Baker,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pewtrusts.org/en/projects/marine-fellows/fellows-directory/2008/andrew-baker|title=Andrew Baker|website=www.pewtrusts.org}}</ref> Ben Kirtman,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rsmas.miami.edu/people/faculty-index/?p=ben-kirtman|title=Ben Kirtman - The Rosenstiel School of Marine and Atmospheric Science at the University of Miami|website=www.rsmas.miami.edu|access-date=2017-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171108185958/http://www.rsmas.miami.edu/people/faculty-index?p=ben-kirtman|archive-date=2017-11-08|url-status=dead}}</ref> and Sala. Topics include education, politics, coral, hurricanes, and urgency.\n\n== Broadcast and streaming ==\nThe film was made available freely on the internet between October 30 and November 6, 2016, the run up to [[United States elections, 2016|US Election Day]], having aired on the National Geographic Channel<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://leonardodicaprio.org/new-documentary-flood-air-globally-natgeo-october-30th/|title=New documentary \"Before The Flood\" to air globally on NatGeo on October 30th - Leonardo DiCaprio Foundation : Leonardo DiCaprio Foundation|website=leonardodicaprio.org|access-date=2016-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118165443/http://leonardodicaprio.org/new-documentary-flood-air-globally-natgeo-october-30th/|archive-date=2017-01-18|url-status=dead}}</ref> in 171{{nbsp}}countries and on some countries' national television channels.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://media.rtp.pt/extra/estreias/10322/|title=National Geographic Channel e RTP unidas contra as altera\u00e7\u00f5es clim\u00e1ticas - Estreia de \"Before the Flood\" {{!}} Extra {{!}} RTP|date=2016-10-26|newspaper=Extra|language=pt-PT|access-date=2016-12-03}}</ref> The film is subtitled in 45{{nbsp}}languages, making it accessible for non-English audiences.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.francetvinfo.fr/monde/environnement/quatre-fois-ou-leonardo-dicaprio-a-montre-son-engagement-ecologique_1897107.html|title=Avant le film \"Before the Flood\", comment DiCaprio a montr\u00e9 son engagement pour la plan\u00e8te|date=2016-10-30|newspaper=Franceinfo|language=fr-FR|access-date=2016-12-03}}</ref> The film had been watched more than 2{{nbsp}}million times on the day following its release.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://observador.pt/2016/10/31/o-documentario-sobre-alteracoes-climaticas-de-leonardo-dicaprio-chegou-a-internet/|title=Document\u00e1rio de Leonardo DiCaprio sobre altera\u00e7\u00f5es clim\u00e1ticas faz sucesso na Internet|last=Observador|website=Observador|access-date=2016-12-04}}</ref> It is currently available for streaming on [[Disney+]].\n\n== Carbon tax ==\nThe film takes a closer look into the possibility of a carbon tax benefiting the American nation. In addition, they state that, \"the carbon emissions from&nbsp;''Before the Flood''&nbsp;were offset through a voluntary carbon tax.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://carbontax.org|title=Carbon Tax Center \u2013 Pricing carbon efficiently and equitably|website=carbontax.org}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/about/|title=Before the Flood - The Film|website=Before the Flood|access-date=2017-04-03}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\nThe film received mostly positive reviews from critics. On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], it has a 72% approval rating, based on 29 reviews.<ref>{{rottentomatoes|before_the_flood_2016}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], it has a score of 63 out of 100, based on 10 critics, indicating \"Generally favorable reviews.\"<ref>{{metacritic film|before-the-flood}}</ref>\n\n''Before the Flood'' was described as \"surprisingly moving\" in ''[[W (magazine)|W]]''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wmagazine.com/story/leonardo-dicaprios-climate-change-documentary-before-the-flood-is-surprisingly-moving|title=Leonardo DiCaprio's Climate Change Documentary \"Before the Flood\" Is Incredibly Moving|last=Sagansky|first=Gillian|newspaper=W Magazine|access-date=2016-11-01}}</ref> and as \"a heartfelt, decent, educational documentary about the most important issue of our time\" by ''[[The Guardian]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/oct/20/before-the-flood-review-leonardo-dicaprio-climate-change-documentary|title=Before the Flood review \u2013 DiCaprio's level-headed climate change doc|last=Bradshaw|first=Peter|date=2016-10-20|newspaper=The Guardian|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|access-date=2016-11-01}}</ref>\n\n[[Variety (magazine)|''Variety'']] praised the fact that \"given the sincerity of its message, its ability to assemble such a watchable and comprehensive account gives it an undeniable urgency,\" stating that \"where the film succeeds the most is by focusing on the ground-level victims of climate change, whether the polar bears of the Arctic, or the inhabitants of island nations like [[Kiribati]].\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/reviews/film-review-before-the-flood-leonardo-dicaprio-1201897172/|title=Film Review: \u2018Before the Flood\u2019|last=Barker|first=Andrew|date=2016-10-21|newspaper=Variety|language=en-US|access-date=2016-12-04}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Award\n! Date of ceremony\n! Category\n! Recipient(s)\n! Result\n! Ref(s)\n|-\n| [[Evening Standard British Film Awards]]\n| December 8, 2016\n| Best Documentary\n| ''Before the Flood''\n| {{won}}\n| <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/goingout/film/evening-standard-british-film-awards-the-longlist-a3398101.html |title=Evening Standard British Film Awards - The Longlist |newspaper=[[London Evening Standard]] |first=William |last=Moore |date=November 17, 2016 |accessdate=November 29, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Hollywood Film Awards]]\n| November 6, 2016\n| Hollywood Documentary Award\n| [[Leonardo DiCaprio]] and [[Fisher Stevens]]\n| {{won}}\n| <ref name=\"Hollywood\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodawards.com/2016/11/leonardo-di-caprio-and-fisher-stevens-to-be-honored/ |title=Leonardo DiCaprio & Fisher Stevens to Be Honored |date=November 2, 2016 |work=[[Hollywood Film Awards]] |accessdate=November 3, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Main article|Before the Flood (soundtrack)}}\nThe film's soundtrack was written and performed by [[Mogwai]], [[Trent Reznor]], [[Atticus Ross]], and [[Gustavo Santaolalla]].<ref name=hollywood /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.factmag.com/2016/09/09/trent-reznor-mogwai-leonardo-dicaprio-climate-change-documentary/|title=Trent Reznor, Mogwai and more team to score Leonardo DiCaprio climate change documentary|date=9 September 2016|publisher=Factmag}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-music|title=Before the Flood - Music|website=Before the Flood}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official|https://www.beforetheflood.com}}\n* [http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x50unqn_before-the-flood-2016-full-national-geographic-documentary-film-with-leonardo-dicaprio-sous-titres-s_school Before the Flood on Dailymotion]\n* [http://channel.nationalgeographic.com/before-the-flood/ National Geographic's Free to Watch Site hosting 'Before the Flood' until November 7, 2017] - http://natgeotv.com/\n* {{IMDb title|id=5929776}}\n* {{rottentomatoes|before_the_flood_2016}}\n* {{metacritic film|before-the-flood}}\n\n{{Leonardo DiCaprio}}\n\n[[Category:2016 films]]\n[[Category:2016 in the environment]]\n[[Category:American documentary films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about global warming]]\n[[Category:2010s documentary films]]\n[[Category:Global warming]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Leonardo DiCaprio]]\n[[Category:National Geographic Channel]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Trent Reznor]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Atticus Ross]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Fisher Stevens]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Gustavo Santaolalla]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Mogwai]]\n[[Category:Climate change films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2016 film by Fisher Stevens}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Before the Flood'' (film)}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Before the Flood\n| image          = Before the Flood (2016 documentary film) poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Fisher Stevens]]\n| producer       = {{plainlist|\n* Fisher Stevens\n* [[Leonardo DiCaprio]]\n* Jennifer Davisson\n* [[James Packer]]\n* [[Brett Ratner]]\n* Trevor Davidoski\n}}\n| writer         = Mark Monroe\n| starring       = \n| narrator       = Leonardo DiCaprio  \n| music          = {{plainlist|\n* [[Gustavo Santaolalla]]\n* [[Trent Reznor]]\n* [[Atticus Ross]]\n* [[Mogwai]]\n}}\n| cinematography = Antonio Rossi\n| editing        = Brett Banks<br>Geoffrey Rickman<br>Abhay Sofsky<br>Ben Sozanski\n| studio         = [[Appian Way Productions|Appian Way]]<br>[[RatPac-Dune Entertainment|RatPac Documentary Films]]<br>Insurgent Docs<br>Mandarin Film Productions\n| distributor    = [[National Geographic Society|National Geographic Documentary Films]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2016|10|21}}\n| runtime        = 96 minutes<ref name=hollywood>{{cite news |last=DeFore |first=John |date=9 September 2016 |title='Before the Flood': Film Review - TIFF 2016 |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/before-flood-927190 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=10 September 2016 }}</ref>\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n| image_size     = \n}}\n'''''Before the Flood''''' is a 2016 [[documentary film]] about [[global warming|climate change]] directed by [[Fisher Stevens]]. The film was produced as a collaboration between Stevens, [[Leonardo DiCaprio]], [[James Packer]], [[Brett Ratner]], Trevor Davidoski, and Jennifer Davisson Killoran. [[Martin Scorsese]] is an executive producer.<ref name=Imdb>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5929776|title=Before the Flood|accessdate=9 September 2016|publisher=IMDB}}</ref>\n\nThe film premiered at the [[Toronto International Film Festival]] in September 2016, and was released theatrically on October 21, before airing on the [[National Geographic Channel]] on October 30.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/dicaprio-unveils-climate-change-film-before-the-flood/2016/09/09/2d279598-76fb-11e6-9781-49e591781754_story.html |title=DiCaprio unveils climate change film \u2018Before the Flood\u2019 |agency=Associated Press |location=''[[The Washington Post]]'' |date=9 September 2016 |access-date=10 September 2016 }}</ref><ref name=\"national-geographic-2016\">{{cite web|url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/2016/10/obama-leonardo-dicaprio-white-house-lawn-before-the-flood-btf/ |title=President Obama Urges Swift Action on Climate Change |publisher=News.nationalgeographic.com |date= |accessdate=2016-10-24}}</ref> As part of National Geographic's commitment to covering climate change, the documentary was made widely available and free of charge on various platforms.<ref name=\"ecowatch-2016\">{{cite web \n | first = Lorraine | last = Chow\n | title = Watch Leonardo DiCaprio's climate change doc online for free\n | work = EcoWatch\n | date = 25 October 2016\n | url = http://www.ecowatch.com/leonardo-dicaprio-before-the-flood-2062971522.html\n | access-date = 2016-10-27\n}}</ref> \n==Background==\nAt the European [[premiere]] in London in October 2016, DiCaprio introduced the film as follows:\n\n{{quote|''Before The Flood'' is the product of an incredible three-year journey that took place with my co-creator and director Fisher Stevens. We went to every corner of the globe to document the devastating impacts of climate change and questioned humanity's ability to reverse what may be the most catastrophic problem mankind has ever faced. There was a lot to take in. All that we witnessed on this journey shows us that our world's climate is incredibly interconnected and that it is at urgent breaking point.{{nbsp}}... We wanted to create a film that gave people a sense of urgency, that made them understand what particular things are going to solve this problem. We bring up the issue of a carbon tax, for example, which I haven't seen in a lot of documentaries. Basically, sway a capitalist economy to try to invest in renewables, to bring less money and subsidies out of oil companies. These are the things that are really going to make a massive difference.{{nbsp}}... We need to use our vote{{nbsp}}... We cannot afford to have political leaders out there that do not believe in modern science or the scientific method or empirical truths{{nbsp}}... We cannot afford to waste time having people in power that choose to believe in the 2{{nbsp}}percent of the scientific community that is basically bought off by lobbyists and oil companies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecowatch.com/leonardo-dicaprio-before-the-flood-2057070140.html|title=7 Key Scenes in Leonardo DiCaprio's Climate Film 'Before the Flood'}}</ref>}}\n\n==Content==\n[[File:The Garden of Earthly Delights by Bosch High Resolution.jpg|thumb|[[The Garden of Earthly Delights]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-painting/|title=Before the Flood - Painting|website=Before the Flood}}</ref>]]\n\nThe film shows DiCaprio visiting various regions of the globe<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-capsule-before-the-flood-review-20161017-snap-story.html|title=Leonardo DiCaprio crosses the globe in the climate change documentary 'Before the Flood'|last=Times|first=Los Angeles|website=latimes.com|access-date=2016-11-01}}</ref> exploring the impact of [[global warming]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wired.it/attualita/ambiente/2016/10/30/before-the-flood-dicaprio/|title=Guarda Before the Flood, il documentario di DiCaprio contro il cambiamento climatico - Wired|date=2016-10-30|newspaper=Wired|language=it-IT|access-date=2016-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031142830/http://www.wired.it/attualita/ambiente/2016/10/30/before-the-flood-dicaprio/|archive-date=2016-10-31|url-status=dead}}</ref> As a narrator, DiCaprio comments these encounters as well as archive footages. DiCaprio repeatedly references a 15th-century [[triptych]] by [[Hieronymus Bosch]], ''[[The Garden of Earthly Delights]]'', which, he explains, hung above his crib as an infant, and which he uses as an analogy of the present course of the world toward<!-- UK English favours \"towards\" but this is a US film --> potential ruin as depicted on its final panel.<ref>{{cite web|title=DiCaprio\u2019s \u2018Before the Flood\u2019 explores a different inconvenient truth: Human nature|publisher=Fusion|url=http://fusion.net/story/364193/dicaprios-before-the-flood-explores-a-different-inconvenient-truth-human-nature/|accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref> The film also documents, in part, the production of DiCaprio's 2015 film ''[[The Revenant (2015 film)|The Revenant]]''.\n\nDiCaprio's comments and inquiries focus extensively on [[climate change denial]], mostly among corporate lobbyists and politicians of the United States.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/article/leonardo-dicaprio-before-the-flood|title=Leonardo DiCaprio almost died making his documentary Before The Flood|last=Halls|first=Eleanor|newspaper=British GQ|language=en-GB|access-date=2016-11-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ctvnews.ca/entertainment/director-horrified-by-alta-oilsands-scenes-in-dicaprio-s-before-the-flood-1.3132335|title=Director 'horrified' by Alta. oilsands scenes in DiCaprio's 'Before The Flood'|newspaper=CTVNews|access-date=2016-11-10}}</ref>\n\nThey interview with British-born astronaut [[Piers Sellers]], a [[NASA]] scientist who flew on three space missions, discusses his desire to publicize the perils of global warming in the short time he expected he had remaining to live, as he had stage IV pancreatic cancer as he was being filmed. He died on December 23, 2016.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/science/2016/dec/24/climate-scientist-and-nasa-astronaut-piers-sellers-dies-aged-61 Climate scientist and Nasa astronaut Piers Sellers dies aged 61], ''[[The Guardian]]'', December 24, 2016. Retrieved April 23, 2019.</ref>\n\n==Cast==\nAlong with DiCaprio, the documentary's subjects include [[Piers Sellers]], [[Barack Obama]], [[Pope Francis]], [[Sunita Narain]], [[Anote Tong]], [[John Kerry]], [[Elon Musk]], [[Alejandro Gonz\u00e1lez I\u00f1\u00e1rritu]], [[Johan Rockstr\u00f6m]], [[Greg Mankiw]], [[Gidon Eshel]], [[Farwiza Farhan]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/farwiza-farhan/|title=Before the Flood - Farwiza Farhan|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> Ian Singleton,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/doctor-ian-singleton-phd/|title=Before the Flood - Dr. Ian Singleton, Ph.D|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> Lindsey Allen,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/lindsey-allen/|title=Before the Flood - Lindsey Allen|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> Jeremy Jackson,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/jeremy-jackson/|title=Before the Flood - Jeremy Jackson|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> Thomas Esang Remengesau Jr.,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/thomas-esang-tommy-remengesau-jr/|title=Before the Flood - Thomas Esang \"Tommy\" Remengesau, Jr.|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> Alvin Lin,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/alvin-lin/|title=Before the Flood - Alvin Lin|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> [[Ma Jun (environmentalist)|Ma Jun]], [[Michael E. Mann]], [[Philip Levine (politician)|Philip Levine]], [[Jason Box|Jason E. Box]],  Dr. [[Enric Sala]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-experts/doctor-enric-sala/|title=Before the Flood - Dr. Enric Sala|website=Before the Flood}}</ref> [[Michael Brune]], and [[Ban Ki-moon|Ban Ki-Moon]].<ref name=hollywood /><ref name=\"national-geographic-2016\"/>\n\nSubjects for the DVD's extra or deleted scenes include: [[Mark Z. Jacobson|Steven Z. Jacobson]], [[Steven Chu]], Andrew Baker,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pewtrusts.org/en/projects/marine-fellows/fellows-directory/2008/andrew-baker|title=Andrew Baker|website=www.pewtrusts.org}}</ref> Ben Kirtman,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rsmas.miami.edu/people/faculty-index/?p=ben-kirtman|title=Ben Kirtman - The Rosenstiel School of Marine and Atmospheric Science at the University of Miami|website=www.rsmas.miami.edu|access-date=2017-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171108185958/http://www.rsmas.miami.edu/people/faculty-index?p=ben-kirtman|archive-date=2017-11-08|url-status=dead}}</ref> and Sala. Topics include education, politics, coral, hurricanes, and urgency.\n\n== Broadcast and streaming ==\nThe film was made available freely on the internet between October 30 and November 6, 2016, the run up to [[United States elections, 2016|US Election Day]], having aired on the National Geographic Channel<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://leonardodicaprio.org/new-documentary-flood-air-globally-natgeo-october-30th/|title=New documentary \"Before The Flood\" to air globally on NatGeo on October 30th - Leonardo DiCaprio Foundation : Leonardo DiCaprio Foundation|website=leonardodicaprio.org|access-date=2016-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118165443/http://leonardodicaprio.org/new-documentary-flood-air-globally-natgeo-october-30th/|archive-date=2017-01-18|url-status=dead}}</ref> in 171{{nbsp}}countries and on some countries' national television channels.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://media.rtp.pt/extra/estreias/10322/|title=National Geographic Channel e RTP unidas contra as altera\u00e7\u00f5es clim\u00e1ticas - Estreia de \"Before the Flood\" {{!}} Extra {{!}} RTP|date=2016-10-26|newspaper=Extra|language=pt-PT|access-date=2016-12-03}}</ref> The film is subtitled in 45{{nbsp}}languages, making it accessible for non-English audiences.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.francetvinfo.fr/monde/environnement/quatre-fois-ou-leonardo-dicaprio-a-montre-son-engagement-ecologique_1897107.html|title=Avant le film \"Before the Flood\", comment DiCaprio a montr\u00e9 son engagement pour la plan\u00e8te|date=2016-10-30|newspaper=Franceinfo|language=fr-FR|access-date=2016-12-03}}</ref> The film had been watched more than 2{{nbsp}}million times on the day following its release.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://observador.pt/2016/10/31/o-documentario-sobre-alteracoes-climaticas-de-leonardo-dicaprio-chegou-a-internet/|title=Document\u00e1rio de Leonardo DiCaprio sobre altera\u00e7\u00f5es clim\u00e1ticas faz sucesso na Internet|last=Observador|website=Observador|access-date=2016-12-04}}</ref> It is currently available for streaming on [[Disney+]] and [[Netflix]].\n\n== Carbon tax ==\nThe film takes a closer look into the possibility of a carbon tax benefiting the American nation. In addition, they state that, \"the carbon emissions from&nbsp;''Before the Flood''&nbsp;were offset through a voluntary carbon tax.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://carbontax.org|title=Carbon Tax Center \u2013 Pricing carbon efficiently and equitably|website=carbontax.org}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/about/|title=Before the Flood - The Film|website=Before the Flood|access-date=2017-04-03}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\nThe film received mostly positive reviews from critics. On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], it has a 72% approval rating, based on 29 reviews.<ref>{{rottentomatoes|before_the_flood_2016}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], it has a score of 63 out of 100, based on 10 critics, indicating \"Generally favorable reviews.\"<ref>{{metacritic film|before-the-flood}}</ref>\n\n''Before the Flood'' was described as \"surprisingly moving\" in ''[[W (magazine)|W]]''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wmagazine.com/story/leonardo-dicaprios-climate-change-documentary-before-the-flood-is-surprisingly-moving|title=Leonardo DiCaprio's Climate Change Documentary \"Before the Flood\" Is Incredibly Moving|last=Sagansky|first=Gillian|newspaper=W Magazine|access-date=2016-11-01}}</ref> and as \"a heartfelt, decent, educational documentary about the most important issue of our time\" by ''[[The Guardian]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/oct/20/before-the-flood-review-leonardo-dicaprio-climate-change-documentary|title=Before the Flood review \u2013 DiCaprio's level-headed climate change doc|last=Bradshaw|first=Peter|date=2016-10-20|newspaper=The Guardian|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|access-date=2016-11-01}}</ref>\n\n[[Variety (magazine)|''Variety'']] praised the fact that \"given the sincerity of its message, its ability to assemble such a watchable and comprehensive account gives it an undeniable urgency,\" stating that \"where the film succeeds the most is by focusing on the ground-level victims of climate change, whether the polar bears of the Arctic, or the inhabitants of island nations like [[Kiribati]].\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/reviews/film-review-before-the-flood-leonardo-dicaprio-1201897172/|title=Film Review: \u2018Before the Flood\u2019|last=Barker|first=Andrew|date=2016-10-21|newspaper=Variety|language=en-US|access-date=2016-12-04}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Award\n! Date of ceremony\n! Category\n! Recipient(s)\n! Result\n! Ref(s)\n|-\n| [[Evening Standard British Film Awards]]\n| December 8, 2016\n| Best Documentary\n| ''Before the Flood''\n| {{won}}\n| <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/goingout/film/evening-standard-british-film-awards-the-longlist-a3398101.html |title=Evening Standard British Film Awards - The Longlist |newspaper=[[London Evening Standard]] |first=William |last=Moore |date=November 17, 2016 |accessdate=November 29, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Hollywood Film Awards]]\n| November 6, 2016\n| Hollywood Documentary Award\n| [[Leonardo DiCaprio]] and [[Fisher Stevens]]\n| {{won}}\n| <ref name=\"Hollywood\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodawards.com/2016/11/leonardo-di-caprio-and-fisher-stevens-to-be-honored/ |title=Leonardo DiCaprio & Fisher Stevens to Be Honored |date=November 2, 2016 |work=[[Hollywood Film Awards]] |accessdate=November 3, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Main article|Before the Flood (soundtrack)}}\nThe film's soundtrack was written and performed by [[Mogwai]], [[Trent Reznor]], [[Atticus Ross]], and [[Gustavo Santaolalla]].<ref name=hollywood /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.factmag.com/2016/09/09/trent-reznor-mogwai-leonardo-dicaprio-climate-change-documentary/|title=Trent Reznor, Mogwai and more team to score Leonardo DiCaprio climate change documentary|date=9 September 2016|publisher=Factmag}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beforetheflood.com/explore/the-music|title=Before the Flood - Music|website=Before the Flood}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official|https://www.beforetheflood.com}}\n* [http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x50unqn_before-the-flood-2016-full-national-geographic-documentary-film-with-leonardo-dicaprio-sous-titres-s_school Before the Flood on Dailymotion]\n* [http://channel.nationalgeographic.com/before-the-flood/ National Geographic's Free to Watch Site hosting 'Before the Flood' until November 7, 2017] - http://natgeotv.com/\n* {{IMDb title|id=5929776}}\n* {{rottentomatoes|before_the_flood_2016}}\n* {{metacritic film|before-the-flood}}\n\n{{Leonardo DiCaprio}}\n\n[[Category:2016 films]]\n[[Category:2016 in the environment]]\n[[Category:American documentary films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about global warming]]\n[[Category:2010s documentary films]]\n[[Category:Global warming]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Leonardo DiCaprio]]\n[[Category:National Geographic Channel]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Trent Reznor]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Atticus Ross]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Fisher Stevens]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Gustavo Santaolalla]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Mogwai]]\n[[Category:Climate change films]]\n", "name_user": "420 L1ghtn1ng mcqueen 420", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBroadcast and streaming:Removed he 'available on netflix.' (no longer avaliable)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Before_the_Flood_(film)"}
{"title_page": "2015 University of Oklahoma Sigma Alpha Epsilon racism incident", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\nThe '''University of Oklahoma Sigma Alpha Epsilon racist incident''', known as ''\"SAE-OU racist chant incident\"'' occurred on March 7, 2015, when members of the [[University of Oklahoma]] (OU) chapter of [[Sigma Alpha Epsilon]] (SAE) were filmed performing a racially insensitive song that used the word \"nigger\" and referenced [[Jim Crow]].\n\nAfter a video of the incident was published, the SAE's OU chapter was closed and two of its members, Levi Pettit and Parker Rice (the latter of whom was the 'leader' of the chant in the video), were expelled.\n\n==Incidents recorded on video==\nOn March 7, 2015, videos were recorded while fraternity members and their dates were riding on a chartered bus to an event celebrating the national organization's Founder's Day. In the video the students are heard singing a chant to the tune of \"[[If You're Happy and You Know It]]\". The chant begins with the [[refrain]], \"There will never be a [[nigger]] at [[Sigma Alpha Epsilon|SAE]]\", which is followed by the lyrics, \"You can hang them from a tree, but they'll never sign with me\", followed again by the refrain. The chant also referenced two key elements of the [[Jim Crow laws|Jim Crow]] era; [[lynching]] ''(You can hang them from a tree)'' and [[racial segregation]] ''(but they'll never sign with me)'', in the form of denial of admission to people of color (African Americans in this case) or any ethnicity other than white into the fraternity.<ref name=dailynews1>{{cite news |title=University of Oklahoma president evicts Sigma Alpha Epsilon brothers from campus frat house after racist video |first=Meg |last=Wagner |date=March 10, 2015 |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/ou-president-evicts-sigma-alpha-epsilon-frat-house-article-1.2142516|work=New York Daily News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Jake |last=New |date=March 8, 2015 |url=https://www.insidehighered.com/quicktakes/2015/03/09/fraternity-caught-video-singing-racist-song|title=Fraternity Caught on Video Singing Racist Song|work=InsideHigherEd.com|accessdate=March 12, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe video of the incident was reported on by ''[[The Oklahoma Daily]]'' on Sunday March 8, and also posted online by student group OU Unheard.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/mar/09/university-oklahoma-fraternity-racism-bigots | title=Oklahoma fraternity's 'racists and bigots' condemned as protests grow |first=Jessica |last=Glenza | newspaper=The Guardian | date=March 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nAn additional video emerged showing the fraternity's house mother, Beauton Gilbow, using the same word \"nigger\" while singing along to a rap song at the fraternity in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/11/us/university-of-oklahoma-sigma-alpha-epsilon-racist-fraternity-video.html |title= As Two Oklahoma Students Are Expelled for Racist Chant, Sigma Alpha Epsilon Vows Wider Inquiry  |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=March 11, 2015 |accessdate=March 11, 2015 |first1=Manny |last1=Fernandez |first2=Richard |last2=P\u00e9rez-Pe\u00f1a}}</ref> Gilbow later stated that she was singing along at the time to rapper [[Trinidad James]]' song \"[[All Gold Everything]]\", which heavily uses the same racial pejorative, and apologized for any offense.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://talkingpointsmemo.com/livewire/beauton-gilbow-statement-rap-video |title=Fraternity 'Mom' Is 'Heartbroken' Over Video That Shows Her Singing N-Word |work=[[Talking Points Memo]] |first=Catherine |last=Thompson |date=March 11, 2015 |accessdate=March 11, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n==Aftermath==\n===SAE chapter suspended===\nOn March 8, 2015, the national office of Sigma Alpha Epsilon closed the OU Chapter house, and OU officials gave SAE members until the end of March 10, 2015 to move out.<ref>{{cite news|last1=McLaughlin|first1=Eliott C.|title='Disgraceful' University of Oklahoma fraternity shuttered after racist chant|url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/03/09/us/oklahoma-fraternity-chant/|accessdate=March 13, 2015 |website=cnn.com |publisher=CNN|date=March 10, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news |url=http://www.oudaily.com/news/parker-rice-identified-as-student-expelled-from-ou-after-racist/article_424a63fc-c74c-11e4-8f34-03aacf374cdb.html |title=Parker Rice identified as student expelled from OU after racist chant |work=OU Daily |author=OU Staff |date=March 10, 2015 |accessdate=March 10, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nTwo days later, OU Facilities Management removed the fraternity's Greek letters from the house. They later put a padlock on the facility's gate, blocked off the parking lot with barriers and caution tape and changed the locks.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.oudaily.com/news/sigma-alpha-epsilon-members-remove-last-of-their-belongings-from/article_6646e9de-c7b4-11e4-9719-bb5ce1fa2405.html |title= Sigma Alpha Epsilon members remove last of their belongings from frat house  |work=OU Daily |first=Daisy |last=Creager |date=March 11, 2015 |accessdate=March 11, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nAt a March 18 press conference, the national SAE office apologized and vowed to promote diversity.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://m.ibtimes.com/sigma-alpha-epsilon-apology-announcement-sae-fraternity-vows-promote-diversity-after-1851198 | title=Sigma Alpha Epsilon Apology Announcement: SAE Fraternity Vows To Promote Diversity After Racist Chant Video | date=March 18, 2015 | newspaper=International Business Times |first= Cristina |last=Silva}}</ref>  The fraternity strongly denied that members had been taught the song, and stated they were investigating additional racist incidents.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/03/11/sigma-alpha-epsilon-says-its-investigating-additional-racist-incidents/ | title=Sigma Alpha Epsilon says it's investigating additional racist 'incidents' | date=March 11, 2015 |first=Fred |last=Barbash | newspaper=The Washington Post}}</ref>  Elsewhere, the University of Texas said it was looking into claims the chant was used by SAE members there.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-oklahoma-fraternity-racist-chant-20150311-story.html | newspaper=LA Times | title=Racist fraternity chant may not be limited to University of Oklahoma | date=March 11, 2015 |first1=Hailey |last1=Branson-Potts |first2=Nigel |last2=Duara |first3=Matt |last3=Pearce }}</ref>\n\n===Students expelled===\nUniversity of Oklahoma president [[David Boren]] ordered the expulsion of two students, Levi Pettit<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/levi-pettit-frat-member-sae-racist-chant-video-deeply-sorry-n330226|title=Levi Pettit, Frat Member in SAE Racist Chant Video, 'Deeply Sorry'|website=NBC News}}</ref> and Parker Rice.<ref name=\"auto1\"/> Through two letters addressed to them, Boren stated that the expulsion was deemed proper as they \"played a leadership role\" in creating \"an extremely hostile learning environment\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/university-oklahoma-racist-fraternity-video-2-sae-students-expelled-leadership-role-1842412|title=University Of Oklahoma Racist Fraternity Video: 2 SAE Students Expelled For 'Leadership Role' |first=Julia |last=Glum |date=March 10, 2015|work=International Business Times}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/levi-pettit-frat-member-sae-racist-chant-video-deeply-sorry-n330226|title = Levi Pettit, Ex-OU Student in SAE Racist Chant Video, 'Deeply Sorry'|date = March 25, 2015|accessdate = March 25, 2015|website = NBC News}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\"/>  The action taken by the university was based on school's Student Rights & Responsibilities Code.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.ou.edu/content/dam/studentlife/documents/AllCampusStudentCode.pdf|title = Student Rights and Responsibilities Code 2014-2015|date = September 19, 2011|accessdate = March 11, 2015|website = University of Oklahoma}}</ref><ref name=\"Feldman\">{{cite news|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/opinion/commentary/ct-oklahoma-university-frat-free-speech-sigma-alpha-epsoilon-perspec-0312-20150311-story.html|title=Balancing the First Amendment vs. racist chants at the University of Oklahoma|last=Feldman|first=Noah|authorlink = Noah Feldman|date=March 11, 2015|work=Chicago Tribune|accessdate=March 14, 2015}}</ref> <ref name=latimes>{{cite news | title=Is University of Oklahoma frat's racist chant protected by 1st Amendment? |first=Matt |last=Pearce| url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-oklahoma-fraternity-explainer-20150310-story.html#page=1 | newspaper=LA Times | date=March 10, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe LA Times reported that Boren appeared to be alluding to Title VI of the Civil Rights Act, which bans racial discrimination at universities receiving federal money.<ref name=latimes />  However, the expulsions may have been a violation of the students' [[first amendment]] rights.<ref name=latimes />  First Amendment law specialist and [[UCLA School of Law|UCLA Law]] professor [[Eugene Volokh]] asserted that President Boren's actions were unconstitutional.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Volokh|first1=Eugene|title=No, a public university may not expel students for racist speech|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/volokh-conspiracy/wp/2015/03/10/no-a-public-university-may-not-expel-students-for-racist-speech/|department=[[The Volokh Conspiracy]]|work=The Washington Post|accessdate=March 10, 2015|date=March 10, 2015}}</ref> Oklahoma State University media law associate professor Joey Senat stated that the chant was offensive but is still protected [[Freedom of speech in the United States|free speech]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-oklahoma-fraternity-fallout-20150310-story.html|work=Los Angeles Times |accessdate=March 10, 2015|date=March 10, 2015 | title=Expelled University of Oklahoma student in racist chant video 'deeply sorry'}}</ref> [[Glenn Reynolds]], a Professor of Law at the [[University of Tennessee]], expressed the opinion that as a former U.S. senator, Boren should have known that the university was breaking the law in expelling the two students.<ref name=\"glennusatoday\">{{cite web|first=Glenn Harlan |last=Reynolds |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/opinion/2015/03/15/ou-oklahoma-frat-race-free-speech-column/24808377/|title=OU broke the law to avoid bad press|work=[[USA Today]]|quote=Boren's behavior was not only illegal \u2014 and clearly so \u2014 it was also a betrayal of the duty of fairness that he, as a university president, owes to every student enrolled in his university. |date=March 17, 2015|accessdate=March 20, 2015}}</ref>  A Washington Post article reported that a [[Sigma Chi]] fraternity successfully challenged similar action taken against them by [[George Mason University]] in 1992.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/03/11/expelled-oklahoma-students-have-an-excellent-chance-of-succeeding-if-they-sue/ | title=Why expelled Oklahoma frat boys would have an 'excellent chance' in court | date=March 11, 2015 | first=Terrence |last=McCoy | work=[[The Washington Post]] | accessdate=March 17, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nOn March 13, alumni on the board of OU's SAE chapter hired civil rights attorney [[Stephen Jones (attorney)|Stephen Jones]] to look into the legal issues involving the chapter's suspension and eviction of members from its fraternity house at OU campus.<ref name=Ohlheiser>{{cite news|last1=Ohlheiser|first1=Abby|title=Sigma Alpha Epsilon 'not ruling out a lawsuit' against Oklahoma University, says lawyer |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/grade-point/wp/2015/03/13/reports-ous-sigma-alpha-epsilon-fraternity-plans-to-sue-the-university/|accessdate=March 13, 2015|work=The Washington Post|date=March 13, 2015}}</ref>  The national office of SAE stated that it was not involved in retaining Mr. Jones and was unaware of his intentions, and that board officials with the OU local chapter had stopped communicating with them since the chapter was closed on March 9.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sae.net/oklahoma |title= Statement in Response to March 13 Stephen Jones Press Conference  |work=SAE Media Statement |date=March 13, 2015 |accessdate=March 13, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/nation/2015/03/13/oklahoma-fraternity-racist-video/70270048/ |title= Oklahoma fraternity chapter hires high-profile attorney |author=Associated Press |work=The Detroit News |date=March 13, 2015 |accessdate=March 13, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nOn March 25, Levi Pettit apologized publicly for his actions.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2015/03/25/levi-pettit-oklahoma-university/70448880/ | title=Expelled University of Oklahoma student offers apology | work=USA Today | date=March 25, 2015 | accessdate=March 25, 2015 | author=Eversley, Melanie}}</ref> Parker Rice issued an apology earlier on March 10, 2015 and added that he led the chant under the influence of alcohol, while also stating that the chant was \"taught to them\". Protesters later gathered outside the Rice family home in Dallas and protested his actions.\n\nIn response to Rice's apology, a member of the chapter who was not with the members on the bus but was present in the chapter house on the day of the incident, confirmed in an interview that the students and members of the chapter were drinking alcohol in the chapter house before the incident. OU president Boren suspected that the chant was learned on the fraternity's leadership cruise but the SAE national headquarters issued a statement that the chant is not one of their sanctioned songs and they would never allow such chant to be sung, stating that any member or chapter who adopts hostile chants are dealt with severe punishment. However, both the national headquarters and Boren state that the chant was informally shared during the leadership cruise by other members.\n\n===Reactions===\nThe SAE-OU chapter's only two African-American alumni, Jonathan Davis and William Bruce James II, defended the house mother, Beauton Gilbow, over her actions and voiced out their support for the chapter's closure. Davis has stated that his co-members and batch mates in the chapter would never allow discriminatory behaviour to take place while James re-echoed Davis' statements and stated that he disowns the people in the videos.\n\nMeanwhile, a student from the rival [[Oklahoma State University]], who also bears the name Parker Rice, became the subject of hate mail and death threats in a case of mistaken identity. Unlike the Parker Rice in the racist chant who was a Dallas native, the other Parker Rice, was a native of Oklahoma and was an Asian Studies student majoring in Japanese. He admits his membership at the Oklahoma State University chapter of [[Alpha Phi Omega]] while condemning the racist chant incident. The Oklahoma-native Rice later posted on social media that he has no connection to SAE and that he was not the Parker Rice in the video.\n\nIn response to the video the [[Oklahoma Sooners football|Oklahoma Sooners]] college football team held arm-in-arm protest vigils instead of attending practice.<ref>{{cite web | website=espn.go.com |publisher=ESPN | url=http://espn.go.com/blog/big12/post/_/id/97130/sae-video-scandal-could-galvanize-oklahoma-sooners | title=SAE video scandal could galvanize Sooners |first=Jake |last=Trotter | date=March 16, 2015}}</ref>\n\nSeveral news media reports highlighted the fact that SAE, which was founded before the [[American Civil War]] in the South had a history of [[Sigma Alpha Epsilon#Discriminatory incidents|discriminatory incidents]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.slate.com/articles/life/inside_higher_ed/2015/03/behind_the_chant_discrimination_at_oklahoma_s_sae_chapter_goes_deeper_than.html |first=Jake |last=New | title=The Ugly, Racist, Deadly History of Sigma Alpha Epsilon | newspaper=Slate | date=March 13, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Society/2015/0314/University-of-Oklahoma-fraternity-has-history-of-racist-incidents-elsewhere-video | title=University of Oklahoma fraternity has history of racist incidents elsewhere  | newspaper=Christian Science Monitor |first=Brad |last=Knickerbocker | date=March 14, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2015/03/11/us/ap-us-sae-profile.html | title=Fraternity in Racist Video Has Roots in Antebellum South | date=March 11, 2015 | newspaper=The New York Times |author=The Associated Press |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403134300/https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2015/03/11/us/ap-us-sae-profile.html |archivedate=March 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\nRobby Soave of the [[Reason Foundation]] wrote that the OU had failed to expel a freshman football player \"caught on tape punching a female student in the face\" in 2014. He concluded, \"if anybody was going to be railroaded off campus without so much as a hearing, you would think it might be perpetrators of actual violence, rather than perpetrators of offensive speech (which is not actually a category of crime).\"<ref name=\"robbysoave\">{{cite web |first=Robby |last=Soave |url=http://reason.com/blog/2015/03/12/oklahoma-u-expels-racist-students-but-no |title=Oklahoma U. Expels Racist Students, But Not Violent Football Players |website=reason.com |publisher=Reason Foundation \n |date=March 12, 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[Mika Brzezinski]] and [[Joe Scarborough]] of ''[[Morning Joe]]'' television show blamed the fraternity brothers' use of the word on [[hip hop music]].<ref name=\"morningjoe\">{{cite web |first=Meg |last=Wagner |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/morning-joe-hosts-blame-racist-sae-video-rap-music-article-1.2145443 |title=\u2018Morning Joe\u2019 hosts blame racist Sigma Alpha Epsilon video on rap music |work=The New York Daily News |date=March 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alternet.org/video/watch-jon-stewart-destroys-morning-joe-and-fox-blaming-racism-rap|title=Jon Stewart Destroys 'Morning Joe' and Fox for Blaming Racism on Rap|date=March 12, 2015|first=Janet |last=Allon|website=[[AlterNet]]|quote=How can those poor children know wrong from right, after being driven to madness by the irresistible power of the hippity-hoppity?|accessdate=March 23, 2015}}</ref>\n\nActor and [[Delta Tau Delta]] alum [[Will Ferrell]] said the incident might be an argument to end the entire college fraternity system. \"The incident in Oklahoma, that is a real argument for getting rid of the system altogether, in my opinion, even having been through a fraternity,\" he told ''[[The New York Times]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Murphy|first=Mekado|url=http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/03/17/sxsw-2015-will-ferrell-answers-readers-questions/ |title=SXSW 2015: Will Ferrell Discusses Fraternities, 'Get Hard' and More|work=The New York Times |date=March 17, 2015 |accessdate=April 4, 2015}}</ref>\n\nBeginning in 2015, first year students and faculty have been required to take a five-hour course on diversity. Although several news outlets have connected the training to the chanting video, the course was announced in January, prior to the incident, in connection with a rumours of a \"Cowboy and Indians\" theme party being planned by a different fraternity.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bennett|first1=Brittney|title=Alleged \"Cowboys and Indians\" party prompts mandatory diversity trainings|url=http://www.oudaily.com/news/alleged-cowboys-and-indians-party-prompts-mandatory-diversity-trainings/article_655bcaa4-a675-11e4-bd03-9f6f0a45438d.html|accessdate=June 16, 2015|work=OU Daily|date=January 28, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Crabtree|first1=Trent|title=U. of Oklahoma to instate mandatory diversity course|url=http://college.usatoday.com/2015/06/11/u-oklahoma-mandatory-diversity-course/|accessdate=June 16, 2015|work=USA Today|date=June 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Univ. of Oklahoma to require incoming students to take diversity class|url=http://wbay.com/2015/06/08/univ-of-oklahoma-to-require-incoming-students-to-take-diversity-class/|accessdate=June 16, 2015|work=WBAY.com|author=Associated Press|date=June 8, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150609161211/http://wbay.com/2015/06/08/univ-of-oklahoma-to-require-incoming-students-to-take-diversity-class/|archive-date=June 9, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== Chapter house repurposed ===\nOn March 10, 2015, OU regained priority over the property. The former chapter house was leased to SAE by OU and was not SAE property. Instead, the chapter house had always been under the ownership of the University.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.oudaily.com/news/ou-s-former-sae-house-will-hold-a-new-center/article_60952954-e25e-11e5-8816-370ebd1745d0.html|title=OU's former SAE house will hold a new center that promotes inclusion |first=Mary |last=Smith |work=OU Daily|access-date=September 25, 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe outer wall of the building was vandalized with black spray paint on the day of the incident, and was promptly removed by the University.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://newsok.com/article/5399778|title=Oklahoma Daily: Sigma Alpha Epsilon fraternity house vandalized after chapter closure|date=March 9, 2015|work=NewsOK.com|access-date=September 25, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAt the beginning of the 2016 academic semester, the former SAE chapter house became the location for OU's University Community Center, which houses the Disability Resource Center (DRC) and the Student Veterans' Association.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ou.edu/content/drc.html|title=Disability Resource Center|website=www.ou.edu|access-date=September 25, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /> The seizure of the fraternity house became an opportunity for the DRC to expand, since the center was previously a small wing at Goddard Health Center and had been searching for a location to expand to.\n\nWithin the Student Veterans' Association's lounge, there is a small exhibit apart of the Henderson Scholars Program in the lower lobby of the former chapter house, to notable university alumni such as [[Ada Lois Sipuel Fisher]] who performed a significant role in the [[Civil Rights Movement]] in Oklahoma.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.oudaily.com/news/ou-student-veterans-association-opens-lounge-in-former-sae-house/article_f9214918-6a1d-11e6-8896-7727a509a817.html|title=OU Student Veterans Association opens lounge in former SAE house |first=Madison |last=Albertson |work=OU Daily|access-date=September 25, 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Coord|35|12|25|N|97|26|43|W|format=dms|display=title|type:event_region:US-OK}}\n\n{{University of Oklahoma}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:University of Oklahoma Sigma Alpha Epsilon racism incident}}\n[[Category:2015 controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:2015 in Oklahoma]]\n[[Category:African-American-related controversies|2]]\n[[Category:History of racism in the United States]]\n[[Category:Race-related controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:Riots and civil disorder in Oklahoma]]\n[[Category:University of Oklahoma]]\n[[Category:2015 in sports in Oklahoma]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\nThe '''University of Oklahoma Sigma Alpha Epsilon racist incident''', known as ''\"SAE-OU racist chant incident\"'' occurred on March 7, 2015, when members of the [[University of Oklahoma]] (OU) chapter of [[Sigma Alpha Epsilon]] (SAE) were filmed performing a racially insensitive song that used the word \"nigger\" and referenced [[Jim Crow]].\n\nAfter a video of the incident was published, the SAE's OU chapter was closed and two of its members, Levi Pettit and Parker Rice (the latter of whom was the 'leader' of the chant in the video), were expelled.\n\n==Incidents recorded on video==\nOn March 7, 2015, videos were recorded while fraternity members and their dates were riding on a chartered bus to an event celebrating the national organization's Founder's Day. In the video the students are heard singing a chant to the tune of \"[[If You're Happy and You Know It]]\". The chant begins with the [[refrain]], \"There will never be a [[nigger]] at [[Sigma Alpha Epsilon|SAE]]\", which is followed by the lyrics, \"You can hang them from a tree, but they'll never sign with me\", followed again by the refrain. The chant also referenced two key elements of the [[Jim Crow laws|Jim Crow]] era; [[lynching]] ''(You can hang them from a tree)'' and [[racial segregation]] ''(but they'll never sign with me)'', in the form of denial of admission to people of color (African Americans in this case) or any ethnicity other than white into the fraternity.<ref name=dailynews1>{{cite news |title=University of Oklahoma president evicts Sigma Alpha Epsilon brothers from campus frat house after racist video |first=Meg |last=Wagner |date=March 10, 2015 |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/ou-president-evicts-sigma-alpha-epsilon-frat-house-article-1.2142516|work=New York Daily News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Jake |last=New |date=March 8, 2015 |url=https://www.insidehighered.com/quicktakes/2015/03/09/fraternity-caught-video-singing-racist-song|title=Fraternity Caught on Video Singing Racist Song|work=InsideHigherEd.com|accessdate=March 12, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe video of the incident was reported on by ''[[The Oklahoma Daily]]'' on Sunday March 8, and also posted online by student group OU Unheard.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/mar/09/university-oklahoma-fraternity-racism-bigots | title=Oklahoma fraternity's 'racists and bigots' condemned as protests grow |first=Jessica |last=Glenza | newspaper=The Guardian | date=March 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nAn additional video emerged showing the fraternity's house mother, Beauton Gilbow, using the same word \"nigger\" while singing along to a rap song at the fraternity in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/11/us/university-of-oklahoma-sigma-alpha-epsilon-racist-fraternity-video.html |title= As Two Oklahoma Students Are Expelled for Racist Chant, Sigma Alpha Epsilon Vows Wider Inquiry  |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=March 11, 2015 |accessdate=March 11, 2015 |first1=Manny |last1=Fernandez |first2=Richard |last2=P\u00e9rez-Pe\u00f1a}}</ref> Gilbow later stated that she was singing along at the time to rapper [[Trinidad James]]' song \"[[All Gold Everything]]\", which heavily uses the same racial pejorative, and apologized for any offense.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://talkingpointsmemo.com/livewire/beauton-gilbow-statement-rap-video |title=Fraternity 'Mom' Is 'Heartbroken' Over Video That Shows Her Singing N-Word |work=[[Talking Points Memo]] |first=Catherine |last=Thompson |date=March 11, 2015 |accessdate=March 11, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n==Aftermath==\n===SAE chapter suspended===\nOn March 8, 2015, the national office of Sigma Alpha Epsilon closed the OU Chapter house, and OU officials gave SAE members until the end of March 10, 2015 to move out.<ref>{{cite news|last1=McLaughlin|first1=Eliott C.|title='Disgraceful' University of Oklahoma fraternity shuttered after racist chant|url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/03/09/us/oklahoma-fraternity-chant/|accessdate=March 13, 2015 |website=cnn.com |publisher=CNN|date=March 10, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news |url=http://www.oudaily.com/news/parker-rice-identified-as-student-expelled-from-ou-after-racist/article_424a63fc-c74c-11e4-8f34-03aacf374cdb.html |title=Parker Rice identified as student expelled from OU after racist chant |work=OU Daily |author=OU Staff |date=March 10, 2015 |accessdate=March 10, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nTwo days later, OU Facilities Management removed the fraternity's Greek letters from the house. They later put a padlock on the facility's gate, blocked off the parking lot with barriers and caution tape and changed the locks.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.oudaily.com/news/sigma-alpha-epsilon-members-remove-last-of-their-belongings-from/article_6646e9de-c7b4-11e4-9719-bb5ce1fa2405.html |title= Sigma Alpha Epsilon members remove last of their belongings from frat house  |work=OU Daily |first=Daisy |last=Creager |date=March 11, 2015 |accessdate=March 11, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nAt a March 18 press conference, the national SAE office apologized and vowed to promote diversity.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://m.ibtimes.com/sigma-alpha-epsilon-apology-announcement-sae-fraternity-vows-promote-diversity-after-1851198 | title=Sigma Alpha Epsilon Apology Announcement: SAE Fraternity Vows To Promote Diversity After Racist Chant Video | date=March 18, 2015 | newspaper=International Business Times |first= Cristina |last=Silva}}</ref>  The fraternity strongly denied that members had been taught the song, and stated they were investigating additional racist incidents.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/03/11/sigma-alpha-epsilon-says-its-investigating-additional-racist-incidents/ | title=Sigma Alpha Epsilon says it's investigating additional racist 'incidents' | date=March 11, 2015 |first=Fred |last=Barbash | newspaper=The Washington Post}}</ref>  Elsewhere, the University of Texas said it was looking into claims the chant was used by SAE members there.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-oklahoma-fraternity-racist-chant-20150311-story.html | newspaper=LA Times | title=Racist fraternity chant may not be limited to University of Oklahoma | date=March 11, 2015 |first1=Hailey |last1=Branson-Potts |first2=Nigel |last2=Duara |first3=Matt |last3=Pearce }}</ref>\n\n===Students expelled===\nUniversity of Oklahoma president [[David Boren]] ordered the expulsion of two students, Levi Pettit<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/levi-pettit-frat-member-sae-racist-chant-video-deeply-sorry-n330226|title=Levi Pettit, Frat Member in SAE Racist Chant Video, 'Deeply Sorry'|website=NBC News}}</ref> and Parker Rice.<ref name=\"auto1\"/> Through two letters addressed to them, Boren stated that the expulsion was deemed proper as they \"played a leadership role\" in creating \"an extremely hostile learning environment\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/university-oklahoma-racist-fraternity-video-2-sae-students-expelled-leadership-role-1842412|title=University Of Oklahoma Racist Fraternity Video: 2 SAE Students Expelled For 'Leadership Role' |first=Julia |last=Glum |date=March 10, 2015|work=International Business Times}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/levi-pettit-frat-member-sae-racist-chant-video-deeply-sorry-n330226|title = Levi Pettit, Ex-OU Student in SAE Racist Chant Video, 'Deeply Sorry'|date = March 25, 2015|accessdate = March 25, 2015|website = NBC News}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\"/>  The action taken by the university was based on school's Student Rights & Responsibilities Code.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.ou.edu/content/dam/studentlife/documents/AllCampusStudentCode.pdf|title = Student Rights and Responsibilities Code 2014-2015|date = September 19, 2011|accessdate = March 11, 2015|website = University of Oklahoma}}</ref><ref name=\"Feldman\">{{cite news|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/opinion/commentary/ct-oklahoma-university-frat-free-speech-sigma-alpha-epsoilon-perspec-0312-20150311-story.html|title=Balancing the First Amendment vs. racist chants at the University of Oklahoma|last=Feldman|first=Noah|authorlink = Noah Feldman|date=March 11, 2015|work=Chicago Tribune|accessdate=March 14, 2015}}</ref> <ref name=latimes>{{cite news | title=Is University of Oklahoma frat's racist chant protected by 1st Amendment? |first=Matt |last=Pearce| url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-oklahoma-fraternity-explainer-20150310-story.html#page=1 | newspaper=LA Times | date=March 10, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe LA Times reported that Boren appeared to be alluding to Title VI of the Civil Rights Act, which bans racial discrimination at universities receiving federal money.<ref name=latimes />  However, the expulsions may have been a violation of the students' [[first amendment]] rights.<ref name=latimes />  First Amendment law specialist and [[UCLA School of Law|UCLA Law]] professor [[Eugene Volokh]] asserted that President Boren's actions were unconstitutional.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Volokh|first1=Eugene|title=No, a public university may not expel students for racist speech|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/volokh-conspiracy/wp/2015/03/10/no-a-public-university-may-not-expel-students-for-racist-speech/|department=[[The Volokh Conspiracy]]|work=The Washington Post|accessdate=March 10, 2015|date=March 10, 2015}}</ref> Oklahoma State University media law associate professor Joey Senat stated that the chant was offensive but is still protected [[Freedom of speech in the United States|free speech]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-oklahoma-fraternity-fallout-20150310-story.html|work=Los Angeles Times |accessdate=March 10, 2015|date=March 10, 2015 | title=Expelled University of Oklahoma student in racist chant video 'deeply sorry'}}</ref> [[Glenn Reynolds]], a Professor of Law at the [[University of Tennessee]], expressed the opinion that as a former U.S. senator, Boren should have known that the university was breaking the law in expelling the two students.<ref name=\"glennusatoday\">{{cite web|first=Glenn Harlan |last=Reynolds |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/opinion/2015/03/15/ou-oklahoma-frat-race-free-speech-column/24808377/|title=OU broke the law to avoid bad press|work=[[USA Today]]|quote=Boren's behavior was not only illegal \u2014 and clearly so \u2014 it was also a betrayal of the duty of fairness that he, as a university president, owes to every student enrolled in his university. |date=March 17, 2015|accessdate=March 20, 2015}}</ref>  A Washington Post article reported that a [[Sigma Chi]] fraternity successfully challenged similar action taken against them by [[George Mason University]] in 1992.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/03/11/expelled-oklahoma-students-have-an-excellent-chance-of-succeeding-if-they-sue/ | title=Why expelled Oklahoma frat boys would have an 'excellent chance' in court | date=March 11, 2015 | first=Terrence |last=McCoy | work=[[The Washington Post]] | accessdate=March 17, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nOn March 13, alumni on the board of OU's SAE chapter hired civil rights attorney [[Stephen Jones (attorney)|Stephen Jones]] to look into the legal issues involving the chapter's suspension and eviction of members from its fraternity house at OU campus.<ref name=Ohlheiser>{{cite news|last1=Ohlheiser|first1=Abby|title=Sigma Alpha Epsilon 'not ruling out a lawsuit' against Oklahoma University, says lawyer |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/grade-point/wp/2015/03/13/reports-ous-sigma-alpha-epsilon-fraternity-plans-to-sue-the-university/|accessdate=March 13, 2015|work=The Washington Post|date=March 13, 2015}}</ref>  The national office of SAE stated that it was not involved in retaining Mr. Jones and was unaware of his intentions, and that board officials with the OU local chapter had stopped communicating with them since the chapter was closed on March 9.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sae.net/oklahoma |title= Statement in Response to March 13 Stephen Jones Press Conference  |work=SAE Media Statement |date=March 13, 2015 |accessdate=March 13, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/nation/2015/03/13/oklahoma-fraternity-racist-video/70270048/ |title= Oklahoma fraternity chapter hires high-profile attorney |author=Associated Press |work=The Detroit News |date=March 13, 2015 |accessdate=March 13, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nOn March 25, Levi Pettit apologized publicly for his actions.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2015/03/25/levi-pettit-oklahoma-university/70448880/ | title=Expelled University of Oklahoma student offers apology | work=USA Today | date=March 25, 2015 | accessdate=March 25, 2015 | author=Eversley, Melanie}}</ref> Parker Rice issued an apology earlier on March 10, 2015 and added that he led the chant under the influence of alcohol, while also stating that the chant was \"taught to them\". Protesters later gathered outside the Rice family home in Dallas and protested his actions.\n\nIn response to Rice's apology, a member of the chapter who was not with the members on the bus but was present in the chapter house on the day of the incident, confirmed in an interview that the students and members of the chapter were drinking alcohol in the chapter house before the incident. OU president Boren suspected that the chant was learned on the fraternity's leadership cruise but the SAE national headquarters issued a statement that the chant is not one of their sanctioned songs and they would never allow such chant to be sung, stating that any member or chapter who adopts hostile chants are dealt with severe punishment. However, both the national headquarters and Boren state that the chant was informally shared during the leadership cruise by other members.\n\n===Reactions===\nThe SAE-OU chapter's only two African-American alumni, Jonathan Davis and William Bruce James II, defended the house mother, Beauton Gilbow, over her actions and voiced out their support for the chapter's closure. Davis has stated that his co-members and batch mates in the chapter would never allow discriminatory behaviour to take place while James re-echoed Davis' statements and stated that he disowns the people in the videos.\n\nMeanwhile, a student from the rival [[Oklahoma State University]], who also bears the name Parker Rice, became the subject of hate mail and death threats in a case of mistaken identity. Unlike the Parker Rice in the racist chant who was a Dallas native, the other Parker Rice, was a native of Oklahoma and was an Asian Studies student majoring in Japanese. He admits his membership at the Oklahoma State University chapter of [[Alpha Phi Omega]] while condemning the racist chant incident. The Oklahoma-native Rice later posted on social media that he has no connection to SAE and that he was not the Parker Rice in the video.\n\nIn response to the video the [[Oklahoma Sooners football|Oklahoma Sooners]] college football team held arm-in-arm protest vigils instead of attending practice.<ref>{{cite web | website=espn.go.com |publisher=ESPN | url=http://espn.go.com/blog/big12/post/_/id/97130/sae-video-scandal-could-galvanize-oklahoma-sooners | title=SAE video scandal could galvanize Sooners |first=Jake |last=Trotter | date=March 16, 2015}}</ref>\n\nSeveral news media reports highlighted the fact that SAE, which was founded before the [[American Civil War]] in the South had a history of [[Sigma Alpha Epsilon#Discriminatory incidents|discriminatory incidents]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.slate.com/articles/life/inside_higher_ed/2015/03/behind_the_chant_discrimination_at_oklahoma_s_sae_chapter_goes_deeper_than.html |first=Jake |last=New | title=The Ugly, Racist, Deadly History of Sigma Alpha Epsilon | newspaper=Slate | date=March 13, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Society/2015/0314/University-of-Oklahoma-fraternity-has-history-of-racist-incidents-elsewhere-video | title=University of Oklahoma fraternity has history of racist incidents elsewhere  | newspaper=Christian Science Monitor |first=Brad |last=Knickerbocker | date=March 14, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2015/03/11/us/ap-us-sae-profile.html | title=Fraternity in Racist Video Has Roots in Antebellum South | date=March 11, 2015 | newspaper=The New York Times |author=The Associated Press |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403134300/https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2015/03/11/us/ap-us-sae-profile.html |archivedate=March 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\nRobby Soave of the [[Reason Foundation]] wrote that the OU had failed to expel a freshman football player \"caught on tape punching a female student in the face\" in 2014. He concluded, \"if anybody was going to be railroaded off campus without so much as a hearing, you would think it might be perpetrators of actual violence, rather than perpetrators of offensive speech (which is not actually a category of crime).\"<ref name=\"robbysoave\">{{cite web |first=Robby |last=Soave |url=http://reason.com/blog/2015/03/12/oklahoma-u-expels-racist-students-but-no |title=Oklahoma U. Expels Racist Students, But Not Violent Football Players |website=reason.com |publisher=Reason Foundation \n |date=March 12, 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[Mika Brzezinski]] and [[Joe Scarborough]] of ''[[Morning Joe]]'' television show blamed the fraternity brothers' use of the word on [[hip hop music]].<ref name=\"morningjoe\">{{cite web |first=Meg |last=Wagner |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/morning-joe-hosts-blame-racist-sae-video-rap-music-article-1.2145443 |title=\u2018Morning Joe\u2019 hosts blame racist Sigma Alpha Epsilon video on rap music |work=The New York Daily News |date=March 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alternet.org/video/watch-jon-stewart-destroys-morning-joe-and-fox-blaming-racism-rap|title=Jon Stewart Destroys 'Morning Joe' and Fox for Blaming Racism on Rap|date=March 12, 2015|first=Janet |last=Allon|website=[[AlterNet]]|quote=How can those poor children know wrong from right, after being driven to madness by the irresistible power of the hippity-hoppity?|accessdate=March 23, 2015}}</ref>\n\nActor and [[Delta Tau Delta]] alum [[Will Ferrell]] said the incident might be an argument to end the entire college fraternity system. \"The incident in Oklahoma, that is a real argument for getting rid of the system altogether, in my opinion, even having been through a fraternity,\" he told ''[[The New York Times]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Murphy|first=Mekado|url=http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/03/17/sxsw-2015-will-ferrell-answers-readers-questions/ |title=SXSW 2015: Will Ferrell Discusses Fraternities, 'Get Hard' and More|work=The New York Times |date=March 17, 2015 |accessdate=April 4, 2015}}</ref>\n\nBeginning in 2015, first year students and faculty have been required to take a five-hour course on diversity. Although several news outlets have connected the training to the chanting video, the course was announced in January, prior to the incident, in connection with a rumours of a \"Cowboy and Indians\" theme party being planned by a different fraternity.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bennett|first1=Brittney|title=Alleged \"Cowboys and Indians\" party prompts mandatory diversity trainings|url=http://www.oudaily.com/news/alleged-cowboys-and-indians-party-prompts-mandatory-diversity-trainings/article_655bcaa4-a675-11e4-bd03-9f6f0a45438d.html|accessdate=June 16, 2015|work=OU Daily|date=January 28, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Crabtree|first1=Trent|title=U. of Oklahoma to instate mandatory diversity course|url=http://college.usatoday.com/2015/06/11/u-oklahoma-mandatory-diversity-course/|accessdate=June 16, 2015|work=USA Today|date=June 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Univ. of Oklahoma to require incoming students to take diversity class|url=http://wbay.com/2015/06/08/univ-of-oklahoma-to-require-incoming-students-to-take-diversity-class/|accessdate=June 16, 2015|work=WBAY.com|author=Associated Press|date=June 8, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150609161211/http://wbay.com/2015/06/08/univ-of-oklahoma-to-require-incoming-students-to-take-diversity-class/|archive-date=June 9, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== Chapter house repurposed ===\nOn March 10, 2015, OU regained priority over the property. The former chapter house was leased to SAE by OU and was not SAE property. Instead, the chapter house had always been under the ownership of the University.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.oudaily.com/news/ou-s-former-sae-house-will-hold-a-new-center/article_60952954-e25e-11e5-8816-370ebd1745d0.html|title=OU's former SAE house will hold a new center that promotes inclusion|last=reporter|first=Mary Smith, news|work=OU Daily|access-date=September 25, 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe outer wall of the building was vandalized with black spray paint on the day of the incident, and was promptly removed by the University.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://newsok.com/article/5399778|title=Oklahoma Daily: Sigma Alpha Epsilon fraternity house vandalized after chapter closure|date=March 9, 2015|work=NewsOK.com|access-date=September 25, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAt the beginning of the 2016 academic semester, the former SAE chapter house became the location for OU's University Community Center, which houses the Disability Resource Center (DRC) and the Student Veterans' Association.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ou.edu/content/drc.html|title=Disability Resource Center|website=www.ou.edu|access-date=September 25, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /> The seizure of the fraternity house became an opportunity for the DRC to expand, since the center was previously a small wing at Goddard Health Center and had been searching for a location to expand to.\n\nWithin the Student Veterans' Association's lounge, there is a small exhibit apart of the Henderson Scholars Program in the lower lobby of the former chapter house, to notable university alumni such as [[Ada Lois Sipuel Fisher]] who performed a significant role in the [[Civil Rights Movement]] in Oklahoma.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.oudaily.com/news/ou-student-veterans-association-opens-lounge-in-former-sae-house/article_f9214918-6a1d-11e6-8896-7727a509a817.html|title=OU Student Veterans Association opens lounge in former SAE house|last=reporter|first=Madison Albertson, news|work=OU Daily|access-date=September 25, 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Coord|35|12|25|N|97|26|43|W|format=dms|display=title|type:event_region:US-OK}}\n\n{{University of Oklahoma}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:University of Oklahoma Sigma Alpha Epsilon racism incident}}\n[[Category:2015 controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:2015 in Oklahoma]]\n[[Category:African-American-related controversies|2]]\n[[Category:History of racism in the United States]]\n[[Category:Race-related controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:Riots and civil disorder in Oklahoma]]\n[[Category:University of Oklahoma]]\n[[Category:2015 in sports in Oklahoma]]\n", "name_user": "Alaney2k", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eChapter house repurposed:cite params", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2015_University_of_Oklahoma_Sigma_Alpha_Epsilon_racism_incident"}
{"title_page": "Ariana Grande discography", "text_new": "{{pp-semi-sock|small=yes}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist            = [[Ariana Grande]]\n| Image             = Ariana Grande (32426962484) (cropped).jpg\n| Caption           = Grande during the [[Dangerous Woman Tour]] in [[Manchester, New Hampshire]] in 2017\n| Alt               = Grande looking in the crowd, while performing\n| Studio            = 5\n| Compilation       = 1\n| EP                = 2\n| Singles           = 45<!-- as of \"Good as Hell (Remix)\" (includes singles as featured artist)-->\n| Option name        = Live albums\n| Option             = 1\n| 1Option name       = Remix albums\n| 1Option            = 1\n| 2Option name      = Promotional singles\n| 2Option           = 8<!-- as of \"Monopoly\"-->\n| 3Option name      = Music videos\n| 3Option           = 40<!-- as of \"Don't Call Me Angel\" (includes videos as featured artist)-->\n}}\n\nAmerican singer [[Ariana Grande]] has released five [[studio albums]], one [[compilation album]], one [[live album]], one [[remix album]], two [[extended play]]s (EPs), forty-six [[single (music)|singles]] (including thirteen as a featured artist), seven [[promotional single]]s and forty [[music video]]s. After signing with [[Republic Records]], she released her debut single \"[[Put Your Hearts Up]]\" in December 2011.\n\nIn April 2013, Grande made her chart debut with \"[[The Way (Ariana Grande song)|The Way]]\",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1555888/macklemore-ryan-lewis-top-hot-100-imagine-dragons-ariana-grande-hit-top-10|title=Macklemore & Ryan Lewis Top Hot 100; Imagine Dragons, Ariana Grande Hit Top 10|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=April 3, 2013|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=May 5, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170214212901/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1555888/macklemore-ryan-lewis-top-hot-100-imagine-dragons-ariana-grande-hit-top-10|archivedate=February 14, 2017}}</ref> which peaked at number nine on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] songs chart in the United States.<ref name=\"US-100\"/> Her debut studio album, ''[[Yours Truly (Ariana Grande album)|Yours Truly]]'', reached the top ten in many countries while debuting at number one on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] albums chart,<ref>{{cite web|author=Billboard Staff|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5687385/ladies-first-quiz-ariana-grande-15-no-1-female-debut-albums|title=Ladies First Quiz: Ariana Grande & 15 No. 1 Female Debut Albums|date=September 11, 2013|work=Billboard|accessdate=September 11, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170106092349/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5687385/ladies-first-quiz-ariana-grande-15-no-1-female-debut-albums|archivedate=January 6, 2017}}</ref> and was subsequently certified Platinum in the US by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA).<ref name=\"RIAA\"/> The album spawned two more singles in 2013: \"[[Baby I]]\" and \"[[Right There (Ariana Grande song)|Right There]]\", the former peaked at number six in Japan.<ref name=\"JPN-sin\"/> In December 2013, Grande released her first extended play, ''[[Christmas Kisses (EP)|Christmas Kisses]]'', featuring four [[Christmas music|Christmas]]-themed tracks.<ref name=\"CK1\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/christmas-kisses-ep/id775223391|title=Christmas Kisses \u2013 EP by Ariana Grande|work=[[iTunes Store]]|date=December 17, 2013|accessdate=September 6, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150715161139/https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/christmas-kisses-ep/id775223391|archivedate=July 15, 2015}}</ref> The EP was re-released in December 2014, exclusive to Japan, with one bonus track, Grande's Christmas single \"[[Santa Tell Me]]\".<ref name=\"JPNCD\">{{cite web|title=CDJapan: Christmas Kisses by Ariana Grande|url=http://www.cdjapan.co.jp/product/UICU-1261|work=Universal Music Japan|accessdate=December 10, 2014}}</ref>\n\nGrande released her second studio album, ''[[My Everything (Ariana Grande album)|My Everything]]'', in August 2014. The material became her second consecutive number-one record on the ''Billboard'' 200.<ref>{{cite web|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|title=Ariana Grande Nabs Second No. 1 Album In Less Than A Year|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6236678/ariana-grande-no-1-album-brad-paisley-kem|work=Billboard|date=September 2, 2014|accessdate=September 3, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708070723/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6236678/ariana-grande-no-1-album-brad-paisley-kem|archivedate=July 8, 2017}}</ref> Its lead single, \"[[Problem (Ariana Grande song)|Problem]]\", was an international hit and reached the top 10 of most major music charts worldwide,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://swedishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Ariana+Grande+feat%2E+Iggy+Azalea&titel=Problem&cat=s | title=Ariana Grande feat. Iggy Azalea \u2013 'Problem' (song) | publisher=Hung Medien | work=swedishcharts.com | accessdate=July 11, 2014}}</ref> including number two in the United States<ref name=\"US-100\"/> and number one in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lane|first=Daniel|title=Ariana Grande earns a place in Official Chart history with Problem|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/ariana-grande-earns-a-place-in-official-chart-history-with-problem-3146/|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|date=June 7, 2014|accessdate=July 7, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170601175201/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/ariana-grande-earns-a-place-in-official-chart-history-with-problem__4302/|archivedate=June 1, 2017}}</ref> The subsequent two singles, \"[[Break Free (song)|Break Free]]\" and \"[[Bang Bang (Jessie J, Ariana Grande and Nicki Minaj song)|Bang Bang]]\", also achieved international success and, as \"Problem\", both reached the top five in the United States.<ref name=\"US-100\"/> All three singles managed to chart within the ''Billboard'' Hot 100's top 10 simultaneously, making Grande the second lead female artist to achieve the feat.<ref>{{cite web|last=Trust|first=Gary|title=Ariana Grande, Iggy Azalea Triple Up In Hot 100's Top 10, MAGIC! Still No. 1|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6221978/hot-100-ariana-grande-iggy-azalea-top-10-magic|work=Billboard|date=August 20, 2014|accessdate=August 20, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170218135539/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6221978/hot-100-ariana-grande-iggy-azalea-top-10-magic|archivedate=February 18, 2017}}</ref> The latter single also went to number one in the United Kingdom. The fourth and fifth singles from the album, \"[[Love Me Harder]]\" and \"[[One Last Time (Ariana Grande song)|One Last Time]]\", respectively peaked at number seven and number 13 in the United States,<ref>{{cite web | url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=ariana grande|chart=Hot 100}} | title=Ariana Grande \u2013 Chart History: The Hot 100 | work=Billboard | accessdate=June 7, 2014}}</ref> also making her the only artist to score four top 10 hits on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|author=Stern, Bradley|title=Ariana Grande and the Weeknd's \"Love Me Harder\" Breaks Into the Top 10 of The Billboard Hot 100|url=http://www.idolator.com/7570257/ariana-grande-the-weeknd-love-me-harder-top-10-billboard-hot-100-taylor-swift|work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=November 12, 2014|accessdate=January 16, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170728144624/http://www.idolator.com/7570257/ariana-grande-the-weeknd-love-me-harder-top-10-billboard-hot-100-taylor-swift|archivedate=July 28, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> All the singles from ''My Everything'' have been certified Platinum or more by the RIAA, while the album was certified 2x Platinum.<ref name=\"RIAA\"/> In June 2015, Grande released her first remix album, titled ''[[The Remix (Ariana Grande album)|The Remix]]'', exclusively to Japan, and consisted of tracks from her first two studio albums.<ref name=\"JPN-Al\"/>\n\nGrande's third studio album ''[[Dangerous Woman]]'' was released in May 2016. The record peaked at number two in the United States while topping the charts in the United Kingdom and 12 other countries.<ref name=\"UK-Al\"/> Its [[Dangerous Woman (song)|eponymous lead single]] debuted at number 10 and peaked at number eight on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100,<ref name=\"US-100\"/> making her the first and only artist in the chart's history to debut in the top 10 with the lead single from each of her first three albums.<ref name=\"top10\">{{cite web|title=Rihanna Rules Hot 100 for Fifth Week, Ariana Grande Debuts at No. 10| url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7263992/rihanna-hot-100-no-1-fifth-week-ariana-grande-debuts|work=Billboard|author=Trust, Gary|date=March 21, 2016|accessdate=March 21, 2016| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160424165135/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7263992/rihanna-hot-100-no-1-fifth-week-ariana-grande-debuts|archivedate=April 24, 2016}}</ref> Her next two singles, \"[[Into You (Ariana Grande song)|Into You]]\" and \"[[Side to Side]]\", also achieved commercial success, with both singles entering the top 20 in the United States and the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7581634/hot-100-rae-sremmurd-black-beatles-number-one-again|title=Rae Sremmurd's 'Black Beatles' Tops Hot 100 for Second Week|author=Trust, Gary| date=November 21, 2016|work=Billboard|accessdate=November 21, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202032310/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7581634/hot-100-rae-sremmurd-black-beatles-number-one-again|archivedate=February 2, 2017}}</ref> In February 2017, Grande and [[John Legend]] covered \"[[Beauty and the Beast (Disney song)#Ariana Grande and John Legend version|Beauty and the Beast]]\" for the 2017 [[Beauty and the Beast (2017 film)|live-action adaption of the same name]]. The theme song peaked at number 10 in Japan,<ref name=\"JPN-sin\"/> and was certified gold by the [[Recording Industry Association of Japan]] (RIAJ).<ref name=\"RIAJ\">{{cite web|url=http://www.riaj.or.jp/f/data/cert/hs_search.html|publisher=Recording Industry Association of Japan|language=Japanese|script-title=ja:\u6709\u6599\u97f3\u697d\u914d\u4fe1\u8a8d\u5b9a\u3000\u4e00\u822c\u793e\u56e3\u6cd5\u4eba \u65e5\u672c\u30ec\u30b3\u30fc\u30c9\u5354\u4f1a|accessdate=March 31, 2016}} ''Note: To retrieve all single certifications, 1) type in \u30a2\u30ea\u30a2\u30ca\u30fb\u30b0\u30e9\u30f3\u30c7 in the box \"\u30a2\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3\u30b9\u30c8\", 2) click \u691c\u7d22''</ref> \"[[No Tears Left to Cry]]\", the lead single from her fourth studio album ''[[Sweetener (album)|Sweetener]]'',<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/ArianaGrande/status/986383824127799296|title=Ariana Grande on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=April 17, 2018}}</ref> reached number one in Australia and Norway. The fifth studio album ''[[Thank U, Next]]'' was released in February 2019. The [[Thank U, Next (song)|lead single of the same name]] debuted at number one simultaneously in the US and UK. The next two singles, \"[[7 Rings]]\" and \"[[Break Up with Your Girlfriend, I'm Bored]]\" debuted at number one and number two respectively, in the United States and topped the charts in the United Kingdom.\n\n==Albums==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of studio albums, with selected details, chart positions, sales, and certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:9.5em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:21.5em;\"| Studio album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"10\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Sales\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:13em;\"| [[List of music re